adqlParser.query
Class ADQLConstantValue

java.lang.Object
  adqlParser.query.ADQLConstantValue
All Implemented Interfaces:
ADQLObject, ADQLOperand
public class ADQLConstantValue
extends java.lang.Object
implements ADQLOperand

It represents a string expression (i.e. 'galaxy') or a numeric value (integer (i.e. 12) or double (i.e. 3.14)).
If not specified, the default type is ADQLType.STRING. In other cases you must give explicitly the type thanks to ADQLType.
The NULL value of SQL and ADQL can be created merely by calling the empty constructor.

Version:
06/2010
Author:
Grégory Mantelet (CDS)
See Also:
ADQLOperand, ADQLType
